Police in Busia are holding more than 10 Democratic Republic of Congo nationals who were locked inside a rental house in Legio estate, a few metres from Busia town. They were awaiting to be transported to Nairobi by unknown people.Busia police boss Masai Makau said police launched a crackdown following a tip off from residents.Those arrested include children, women and men who had DRC voting cards.Makau said his officers will continue with the crackdown to track down those engaging in human trafficking.He saidstern legal action will be taken.Makau cautioned boda boda operators said to be ferrying people from Uganda through secret entry points popularly known as &ldquo;panya&rdquo; routes.He said the foreigners pay between Sh1,000 and Sh5,000.